From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fennec Authors <patches@fennec.computer>
Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] networking: block all outbound requests before setup consent

Installs a ConsentFirstNetworkGuard as a URLLoaderInterceptor at the
NetworkService layer. The guard rejects all outbound HTTP/HTTPS requests
until the user completes fennec://setup and the consent record is written
to the profile's SQLite database.

Allowed before consent:
  - fennec:// scheme (WebUI pages — all local)
  - chrome:// scheme (browser infrastructure — all local)
  - data: / blob: / about: (in-process content)

Blocked before consent:
  - ALL http:// and https:// requests — full stop
  - Including requests initiated by Fennec itself (filter list fetches, etc.)
  - Including requests from loaded web pages (setup page makes none anyway)

The guard is removed as soon as setup is complete. Its presence is logged
to the Request Journal as a category-7 (kFennecInternal) administrative
event.

This is the enforcement mechanism that makes tests/zero_requests_test.py
pass by construction, not just by convention.

PILLAR: Transparency / Privacy
JOURNAL: Logs one kFennecInternal event "consent-guard-active" on first
         launch; one "consent-guard-released" on setup completion.

